4. Why rabbits in particular are vulnerable

Rabbits have:
	•	extremely sensitive sympathetic nervous systems
	•	high heart rates
	•	low stress tolerance
	•	prey-animal wiring optimized for freeze-or-flee

Their biology is tuned for:

“Escape instantly or die.”

Under circumstances where escape is impossible, the system sometimes shortcuts to the endpoint.

Not metaphorically.
Literally.

